Body: Less than a day remains till launching the pre-ICO EGH, and the EcoGreenHouse team feels about like Elon Musk and Co. before the start of Falcon in 2015 (there is a video on the net - just watch it). The project has already changed our own lives, but it still has to break the established paradigm that organic vegetables are too difficult, too expensive and unwanted. This is not true! We are ready to prove that greenhouses, designed with the latest engineering findings in mind, and using innovative materials, will allow growing natural vegetables and greens in the true natural soil. Agroinnovations from EGH are easy to scale and implement in any regions of Russia. You can easily become an active participant in this process, even if you do not understand anything in agriculture. Three years ago, when we were at the very start of our project, we had nothing but the desire to put on the table a bowl of fragrant and sweet tomatoes. We have learned from farmers of Russia, Holland and Singapore, we invited the best practitioners to our team, we developed technology and wrote a business plan, and now we take it all to the public. Tomorrow it will become clear how many people are ready to make a small agro-revolution with us. Are you with us?

Author: cbutters
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] 🌿🍅🍆 EcoGreenHouse - Opгaничecкиe пpoдyкты для вac
Body: The launch of pre-ICO has been postponed due to the hackers' attack On September 27th egh.io website incurred a massive DDoS attack. Despite all the efforts of the project team and technical support services that took two days when pre-sale was scheduled to start, we could not restore its work and launch the issue of tokens. It was decided to postpone the start for 10/06/2017. During this time we will carry out the necessary technical improvements of the site and strengthen the perimeter of protection. The first priority is to secure future members of the EGH club and their financial resources. To some extent it is good that the site "fell down" before the start - we received a painful vaccination against future illnesses. Yes, we are terribly upset that we did not met the deadlines, we understand that this could affect the intentions of our potential investors, and we are doing our best to restore confidence in the project.  This forced delay will not become an obstacle to the creation of a network of high-tech greenhouses for growing organic vegetables. None of us, since we are not the first year in business, expected that it would be easy, but only after starting with ICO, we could see what interest it causes in unscrupulous entrepreneurs and outright scammers. By taking EGH to ICO, we want, among other things, to prove that this is an honest, open, legal way of investing in interesting start-ups. The team is full of enthusiasm to bring it to the end and celebrate the victory with sweet aromatic tomatoes along with you.

Author: cbutters
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] 🌿🍅🍆 EcoGreenHouse - Opгaничecкиe пpoдyкты для вac
Body: If you take a look at domestic Russian agricultural research, Russia will seem an all-world champion in everything agriculture: the export of wheat and pork grows day by day, the food stores groan from Russian tomatoes and cheeses thanks to the import substitution, etc. However, if we look a little wider, we will see that agribusinesses in Russia are ineffective. According to J'son & Partners Consulting, the gross value of agricultural products per employee in our country in 2015 was $ 8,000, in Germany $ 24,000, in the US $ 195,000. The developed world enters the era of Agriculture 4.0. Harvest now depends not so much on the diligence of the farmer, but rather on the use of smart technologies: the Internet of things (today every 6th project in the IoT field is implemented in agriculture), analysis of large data, predictive analytics. Agro-market quickly merges with the IT industry which guarantees explosive growth in productivity at lower costs. This explains the high investment attractiveness of the industry. Seven years ago, venture investments in agro-startups did not exceed $ 400,000; in 2015 the market set a record - $ 4.6 billion. Annually 500 new projects emerge, and most start-ups "grow" in the fields of the USA, China, India, Canada, and Israel. Russia still has to strive hard to get to this top. Why? I completely agree with the answer given by J'son & Partners analysts: one of the reasons for Russia's technological backwardness is that cheap and low-quality food products prevail in the structure of consumption in our country. The authors of the study, referring to Rosstat and more respectable sources, say that consumption of meat, dairy products, fruits and vegetables is lower than medical standards, and 2-3 times lower than in the US and Germany. A vicious circle: a farmer is barely making ends meet without having the resources to innovate while quality products are unavailable for a buyer. In a long chain of intermediaries, the price of the crop grows exponentially, but it does not yield much to those working the land directly: 90% of the sales from agricultural products remain in wholesale and retail trade, and with banks. Digitalization can change this. Reduce the supply chain and make all production and logistics processes as open as possible is the main task of our agricultural project, EcoGreenHouse (www.egh.io). The mechanism for this has already been thought up - blockchain. When buying our eco-tokens, you confirm membership in the EGH club and get the opportunity to purchase fresh vegetables grown by organic technology in living soil, at a cost of   25%, which is 5-10 times cheaper than in stores. #EcoGreenHouse, #egh, #ICO

Author: cbutters
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] 🌿🍅🍆 EcoGreenHouse - Opгaничecкиe пpoдyкты для вac
Body: Hi, finally came interesting questions.  1   Yes, we are against GMO. Is it a stereotype or not? Of course, a stereotype, any common point of view is a stereotype. We will admit that the genetically modified plants have not passed the test of time. I personally know a dozen Ph.D. which are against GMO.  2   Automation is widely represented in greenhouses and this is wonderful. We are taking the next step - the machine will answer the question why the crop turned out this way and how to make it better.  3   The financial crisis is very loud words. According to the media, Russia lives in a crisis since 1985. Now only rich people can afford organic produce - it costs 5 times the same weight of vegetables grown in hydroponics. We are creating a club. Members of the club will be able to buy our vegetables at a cost plus 25%. For comparison, in a store, such products cost more than 5-10 times. We want our vegetables to be available to everyone.  4   Large agricultural producers put the number of produced products in the first place and apply different chemistry to achieve the result. If people were judged by their weight, the more, the better, then it is clear what they should eat. Any additives accumulate in the plant and eventually the person eats them. Why do you need chemistry? How will this chemistry behave in your body? For myself, I decided that vegetables without chemicals are my way.  5   The world is moving forward, and today there is an opportunity to attract crowdfunding. What would have happened to Facebook if the IPO had immediately passed? Yesterday, it was right way to attract venture capital, and today crowdfunding.
